## Step-by-Step Plan (Taking It Slow)

Each step is a discrete, completable unit. No step starts until the
previous one is reviewed and confirmed. Screenshots document each.

### Step 1 — Stack Decision (DECIDED)
**Rails.** Vanilla Rails. No JS framework bolted on, no static site
generator. SwarmPod is Rails-native, FolkCoder is Rails-native. One
ecosystem, one language, one set of conventions.

What this means concretely:
- Ruby on Rails 8 (Hotwire/Turbo/Stimulus for interactivity)
- SQLite for dev, Postgres for production
- Import maps (no Node, no Webpack, no esbuild unless forced)
- Rails built-in auth or a simple gem (Devise, or Rails 8 auth generator)
- Hosting TBD (Railway, Render, Fly.io, Hatchbox — all Rails-friendly)
- Domain and DNS setup for folkcoder.com

Remaining decisions for Step 1:
- Hosting provider
- Domain/DNS status (do you already own folkcoder.com?)
- `rails new` now, or after hosting is sorted?

### Step 2 — Landing Page (Homepage)
Implement the homepage from `folkcoder_homepage_content.md`:
- Hero, How It Works, Features, Community, Starting Gate, CTA
- Responsive, clean, no over-engineering
- Deploy to a staging URL

### Step 3 — The /next Page
Implement the post-SwarmPod redirect page from
`folkcoder_next_page_content.md`:
- Congratulations flow, curriculum CTA, registration hook
- Wire the localhost redirect path

### Step 4 — Registration & User Profiles
- Auth system (email, GitHub OAuth)
- Developer profile creation (skills, roles, collaboration style)
- Database and user storage

### Step 5 — AI Infrastructure (Phase 1)
Begin the AI-centered business layer:
- Define what "AI manages the business" means concretely
- Candidate areas: content generation, user matching, onboarding
  automation, support, analytics, sponsor outreach
- Choose tools and APIs (Claude API, automation frameworks)

### Step 6 — Hackathon Hub
- Hackathon directory with search/filter
- Team formation and recruiting boards
- Project showcase pages

### Step 7 — AI Infrastructure (Phase 2)
- Smart team matching
- Curriculum progress tracking
- Automated community management
- Business analytics and reporting

### Future Steps
